While on his weeklong visit to his Daura home in Katsina, President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday presided over the 28th meeting of the Federal Executive Council (FEC).
At the virtual meeting are Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo, the Chief of Staff to the President Ibrahim Gambari, and the National Security Adviser, retired Maj.-Gen. Babagana Monguno—all at the Council Chamber of the Presidential Villa in Abuja    .
Other members of the cabinet present at the meeting include the Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Mr Abubakar Malami, Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, and his Works and Housing counterpart, Mr Babatunde Fashola.
Others like Defence Minister Bashir Magashi, Environment, Mohammed Abubakar, Police Affairs, Maigari Dingyadi, Minister of State, Petroleum Resources, Timipre Sylva, Head of the Civil Service of the Federation, Dr Folasade Yemi-Esan, and other ministers participated from their respective offices.
